Remove the top and bottom from the @courgette{1}. Halve lengthways and chop into 1cm cubes. Halve, then remove the core from the @yellow pepper{1/2} and chop into 1cm cubes as well.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}). Pick the @thyme{1/2} leaves from their stalks (discard the stalks). Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into roughly ½cm pieces.

Put a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add the courgette, pepper, garlic and onion. Season with a pinch of @salt{} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. Cook until everything softens, ~{5%minutes}. Add the @British beef mince{250%g}. Cook until browned, ~{5%minutes}. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

Once the beef has browned add the thyme leaves, @soy sauce{1} and @Italian style herbs{3/4}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add the @chopped tomatoes{1}, season with another pinch of @salt{} and a few more grinds of @black pepper{}. Leave to simmer on medium-low heat until the sauce thickens, ~{15%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a glug of red wine to the ragu if you have some, it will add a great depth of flavour!

Meanwhile, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with a pinch of @salt{}. Add the @wheat spaghetti{200%g} to the boiling water and cook until 'al dente', about ~{10%minutes}.

> TIP: 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle.

Drain the pasta in a #colander{} and toss it in the ragu before serving in #bowls{} and grating over plenty of @parmesan cheese{20%g}. Buon appetito!